### isValidCtxInstructionForOutsideAnalysis() {#ade252ec650f1f043ccf664b66c038d38}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bool anonymous&#95;namespace&#123;AttributorAttributes.cpp&#125;::AAValueConstantRangeImpl::isValidCtxInstructionForOutsideAnalysis (<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/attributor">Attributor</a> &amp; A, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/instruction">Instruction</a> &#42; CtxI, bool AllowAACtxI) const</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Return true if <code>CtxI</code> is valid for querying outside analyses.

This basically makes sure we do not ask intra-procedural analysis about a context in the wrong function or a context that violates dominance assumptions they might have. The <code>AllowAACtxI</code> flag indicates if the original context of this <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/aa">AA</a> is OK or should be considered invalid.
